age" data-gemlang="en" data-width="90%" data-height="auto" title="" width="863" height="797" natural-width="863" natural-height="797"></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1742981559383" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1742981559383"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>2. Push</p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1742981559326" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1742981559326"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Push stick gently against the edge of your nail strip. Nudge strip in direction of your cuticle to minimize damage to your nail. Keep pushing until entire nail strip lifts up and detaches from your nail.</p><p></p></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-3 gf_col-md-3 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1705312628146" data-id="1705312628146"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1742981559315" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1742981559315" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg gf-elm-center-sm" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/5343173b-2694-4870-a9fc-fbf9d0939845/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/3.jpg" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" data-width="90%" data-height="auto" title="" width="863" height="797" natural-width="863" natural-height="797"></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1742981559274" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1